               <head>Mir'at-e Ahmadi in 2 parts</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mirʾāt-i Aḥmadī by ʿAlī Muḥammad Khān</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115302" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3843-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_195021234">ʿAlī Muḥammad Khān</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_195021234">علی محمد خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6999">Mirʾāt-i Aḥmadī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_6999">مرآۃ احمدی</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>History of Gujarat, the <title>Mirʾāt-i Aḥmadī</title>, extending to the defeat of the Marathas by Aḥmad Shāh Abdālī Durr-i Durrān at the battle of Panipat in 1174/1761 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author, ʿAlī Muḥammad Khān, began the work in 1170/1756-7 and completed the historical portion on 10 Ṣafar 1175/9 September 1761 </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into sections: muqaddimah (beginning f. 8v); Hindu rulers (beginning f. 16r); Islamic rulers (beginning f. 20r); khātimah (beginning f. 574r) </p>
                        <p>Volume divided into 2 parts: 3843A (ff. 1-368) and 3843B (ff. 369-725) </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon: 14 Rabīʿ II 1299/5 March 1882 </p>
                        <p>Purchased 15 August 1913 from <persName key="person_59482161" role="fmo">Sir E. Clive Bayley</persName>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
